  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Durable Solutions to Support Conflict-Affected Persons in Overcoming Displacement-Specific Needs in Kirkuk</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Despite the military defeat of the Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant (ISIL), Iraq remains at a critical juncture, with a significant risk of the country backsliding into conflict. Alongside broader efforts to facilitate access to durable solutions, the Government of Iraq and its partners must grapple with the complex question of how families with perceived ties to ISIL can be supported to safely return to and reconcile with their communities in the areas of origin, whilst minimizing the risk of future conflict and (re)recruitment into violent extremist groups. At the same time, the Iraqi authorities are still struggling to manage the fallout of the mass mobilization, which took place to retake large swathes of the country&#x2019;s territory from ISIL. With this project, IOM seeks to increase the durability of results and future durable solutions through a mixture of support for national and local institutions, as well as direct support for affected populations, to strengthen long-term stability in communities of return or local integration.</narrative>
  </description>
